claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: A slide listing key attributes of a recombinant flu vaccine (recombinant HA produced in insect cell culture, 45 µg HA per strain per 0.5 mL dose, no eggs or adjuvants, licensed in 2016 for adults ≥18 years) does not support the claim because the image only provides vaccine product characteristics and contains no comparative immunogenicity or antibody response data Note: Image quality limits detail, but no antibody titer or comparative efficacy data are presented
